.TH PHASORSTD_RAND 3 "January 2026" "Phasor 4.0.0" "Phasor Standard Library 4.0.0"
.SH NAME
phasorstd_rand \- Phasor pseudo-random number generation (xorshift+) functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B using("stdrand");
.PP
.B rand_seed(s1, s2)
.B rand_next_range(min, max)
.B rand_next_float()
.fi
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
.BR rand_seed (s1, s2)
Seed the pseudo-random number generator with two positive integer values. Must be called
before using
.B rand_next_range()
or
.B rand_next_float()
to ensure reproducible sequences.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBs1\fR 12
First seed value; must be a positive non-zero integer
.IP \fBs2\fR 12
Second seed value; must be a positive non-zero integer
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
Null value
.PP
.B Throws:
Runtime error if either seed is not a positive integer.
.RE
.PP
.TP
.BR rand_next_range (min, max)
Generate a pseudo-random integer in the closed interval [\fBmin\fR, \fBmax\fR].
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBmin\fR 12
Lower bound of the range (inclusive). Non-integer values are treated as 0.
.IP \fBmax\fR 12
Upper bound of the range (inclusive). Non-integer values are treated as 0.
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
Integer in the range [\fBmin\fR, \fBmax\fR]
.PP
.B Throws:
Runtime error if
.B min
is greater than
.B max
.RE
.PP
.TP
.BR rand_next_float ()
Generate a pseudo-random float (double-percision) value.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
None
.PP
.B Returns:
float in the range [0.0, 1.0)
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Basic Usage
.PP
.nf
.RS
using("stdrand");

// Seed the generator
rand_seed(123456, 789012);

// Generate a random integer between 1 and 100
var n = rand_next_range(1, 100);
putf("Random number: %d", n);

// Generate a random float
var d = rand_next_float();
putf("Random float: %f", d);
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Reproducible Sequences
.PP
.nf
.RS
// Same seeds always produce the same sequence
rand_seed(42, 1337);
var a = rand_next_range(0, 9);
var b = rand_next_range(0, 9);

rand_seed(42, 1337);
var c = rand_next_range(0, 9);
var d = rand_next_range(0, 9);

// a == c and b == d
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Simulating a Coin Flip
.PP
.nf
.RS
rand_seed(seed1, seed2);

var flip = rand_next_range(0, 1);
if (flip == 0) {
    puts("Heads");
} else {
    puts("Tails");
}
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Scaling a float to a Custom Range
.PP
.nf
.RS
rand_seed(111, 222);

// Random float between 0.0 and 10.0
var scaled = rand_next_float() * 10.0;
putf("Scaled value: %f", scaled);
.RE
.fi
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
The generator must be seeded with
.B rand_seed()
before use; behaviour is undefined if
.B rand_next_range()
or
.B rand_next_float()
are called without a prior seed
.IP \(bu 2
Using the same pair of seeds always produces the same set of values, which is
useful for various purposes.
.IP \(bu 2
Both seeds must be strictly positive; zero and negative values are rejected
.IP \(bu 2
Non-integer arguments to
.B rand_seed()
and
.B rand_next_range()
are silently coerced to 0, which will cause
.B rand_seed()
to throw
